text: Coker is a town in Tuscaloosa County, Alabama, United States. It was incorporated in 1999. At the 2020 census, the population was 904. It is part of the Tuscaloosa Metropolitan Statistical Area. == Geography == Coker is located at (33.246283, -87.679221).
